e, TPPT, on a\ndisordered graphene surface. PPT is seen to form flat structures whilst TPPT is\nseen to form semicircular cone like micelle structures on the graphene surface.\nIn the presence of water, the PPT tends to aggregate whereas the TPPT micelle\nexpands.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 14 Oct 2016 21:39:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-18"}
